modules.description: Maintains a mutable circular linked list with O(1) insertion and deletion at any node, and O(n) traversal across elements. It pairs the linked list with a hashtable for near O(1) lookups by key. Useful for scenarios requiring frequent updates and fast access to elements in a cyclic structure.

Initializes a circular linked list from a standard list, allows traversal and modification with head movement, and provides efficient search and insertion. Operates on a mutable circular linked list structure with elements stored in a node-based format. Enables efficient value lookup and reordering in applications like round-robin scheduling or ordered data navigation.
